When a class has a property with a private **set** accessor, its [PropertyDescriptor's IsReadOnly](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.componentmodel.propertydescriptor.isreadonly?view=netcore-2.1#System_ComponentModel_PropertyDescriptor_IsReadOnly) property returns **false**. The same code evaluates IsReadOnly to **true** in .NET Framework 4.7.2. 
The following code demonstrates the issue:
```
        static void AssertReadOnlyAttribute()
        {
            var foo = new Foo();
            var barProperty = TypeDescriptor.GetProperties(foo).Find("Bar", true);
            System.Diagnostics.Debug.Assert(barProperty.IsReadOnly);
        }

        class Foo
        {
            public bool Bar { get; private set; }
        }
```

